  "monsterText": ["About", "When not disguised as a humanoid, the raja rakshasa has the head of an animal.", "The hands of a raja rakshasa are more subtly unsettling, for the fingers of these fiends bend outward, away from the palms.", "More than any other types of rakshasa, rajas scoff at religion. They understand the power of the divine, yet they view themselves as the only things worthy of worship from mortal creatures; not even their own immortals are deemed deserving of such glorification. Raja rakshasas often form close-knit families that work together to bring down mortal cities or to rule them from the shadows within. Such families of rakshasas often incorporate other breeds of the fiend, often using dandasukas as favored servants or stealthy spies. Even though a raja family works together to achieve a shared goal, infighting and treachery among their own is a constant threat."]
